Open System Interconnection


Layers:

Application => From this the requests are made. (UI)

Presentation => Converts request into ASCII and encrypt if necessary

Session => Initiates a session between networks

Transport => Adds port of both sender and receiver in the request data. This part is called segments.

Network => Segments are splitted in to packets and IP address of both sender and receiver are added in each packet.

Data_link => MAC address of both sender and receiver are added and this layer of data is called Frames.

Physical => Data will in the form of bytes(0's & 1's)